 Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["from <i>frid</i> ‘peace’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power’; a royal and imperial name from an early date."],"variants":[{"name":"Frederick","meanings":["From an Old French name of Germanic origin, from <i>fred</i>, <i>frid</i> ‘peace’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was adopted by the Normans and introduced into Britain by them, but did not survive long. Modern use in Britain dates from the 17th century, and it became more frequent in the 18th among followers of the Elector of Hanover, who in  1714  became  George I  of England. It was reinforced by the vogue for Germanic names in Victorian times."]},{"name":"Friederich","meanings":["from <i>frid</i> ‘peace’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power’; a royal and imperial name from an early date."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Friedrich von Siulichen was born in 1005, in Germany, his father, Hesso I von Sülichgau, was 25 and his mother, Hiltgart von Tübingen, was 23. He had at least 1 son with Irmentrud von Nellenburg. He died on 3 May 1097, in his hometown, at the age of 92."},"et":{"1005–3 May 1097":"1005–3. mai 1097","1001–1061":"1001–1061","1005–1097":"1005–1097","1010–Female":"1010–Surnud","1026–1061":"1026–1061","0980–1035":"0980–1035","0982–Female":"0982–Surnud","1005":"1005","1026":"1026","0982":"0982","1035":"1035","0980":"0980","1001":"1001","1010":"1010","1097":"1097","Abt 1026":"umbes 1026","1061":"1061","3 May 1097":"3. mai 1097","Germany?":"Saksamaa","Nahe, Segeberg, Schleswig-Holstein, Prussia, Germany":"Nahe, Kreis Segeberg, Schleswig-Holstein, Preußen, Saksamaa","Germany":"Saksamaa","Bad Kissingen, Unterfranken, Bavaria, Germany":"Landkreis Bad Kissingen, Bayern, Saksamaa"},"fi":{"1005–3 May 1097":"1005–3. toukokuuta 1097","1001–1061":"1001–1061","1005–1097":"1005–1097","1010–Female":"1010–Kuollut","1026–1061":"1026–1061","0980–1035":"0980–1035","0982–Female":"0982–Kuollut","1005":"1005","1026":"1026","0982":"0982","1035":"1035","0980":"0980","1001":"1001","1010":"1010","1097":"1097","Abt 1026":"noi